          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A 94 mug/cm**2 Sm-144 target isotopically enriched",
                "to 88.6% was used.",
                "Evaporation residues were trapped in a stack of three",
                "aluminized mylar foils, glued together to form a single",
                "catcher foil, which was placed about 3 mm behind the",
                "target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDGT"
                ],
                "institute": "3BZLUSP"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 8-UD Pelletron accelerator."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Silicon surface-barrier detectors were placed",
                "at 45 degree to the beam for monitoring the Rutherford",
                "scattering."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The a 5 cm**3 Ge planar X-ray detector with",
                "energy resolution of 480-eV(FWHM)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "*By authors*.Effects explicitly taken into accoount in",
                "the deduction of the cross sections are-",
                "  -the time dependence of the beam intensity",
                "  -the presence of isomeric states with half-lives of",
                "  several minutes in the decay chains of some of the",
                "  evaporation residues,",
                "  -summing effects due to the simultaneous detection",
                "  of more than one photon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections to the Ho and Dy K(alpha) X-ray yields from",
                "the fusion of O-16 with the 11.4% of other Sm isotopes",
                "present in the target were based on the measured(see",
                "O1608) or interpolated cross sections for these",
                "isotopes. These corrections were relatively small",
                "because the X-ray energy and decay half-life enable one",
                "to discriminate experimentally against the products of",
                "fusion with the heavier isotopes. No corrections need",
                "be made for fusion of the projectile with the light",
                "contaminants in the target because these residues pass",
                "through the catcher fooil. Fission of the compound",
                "nucleus and alpha-particle emission were estimated to",
                "be negligible effects."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Taking into account the sources of random and",
                "systematic uncertainties(excludin beam energy), an",
                "overall error of around 9% in the fusion cross sections",
                "was calculated. The systematic error on the beam energy",
                "is equivalent to a 20% systematic error on the cross",
                "sections for the three lowest bombarding energies."
              ]
            }
          ],
